So i was asked to create a site using webjobs ( webScribble &#8211; http//:webjobs.com ). The client already had a site that was built years ago using webJobs v1 and they wanted to upgrade to the latest version 3. 
The software ( latest version ) is a pretty comprehensive version of jobs webboard where you can quickly generate an all singing all dancing website. It offers lots of features &#8211; integration of feeds from other sites, employer and employee login, online sales, backend CMS /  admin system, social site auto login, iPhone site &#8211; the list goes on for a while.
The basic cost of the software is about $400 and the plugins are all extra.
Its basically a step up from a framework &#8211; or a framework thats been developed into a set of top level tools for site building.]]></content:encoded>
