			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-303" style="vertical-align: top; float: left; margin-right: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;" title="Walking dead" src="http://louiscox.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/wd-300x200.jpg" alt="Walking dead" title="wd" width="300" height="200" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-705" />
Unbeknown to me the series <a href="http://www.amctv.com/originals/The-Walking-Dead/">Walking Dead</a> is based on a <a href="http://www.hiddenrobot.com/WALKINGDEAD/">comic</a> &#8211; which came as a bit of a shock, and Im not exactly a stranger to comics having been a lifelong reader of <a href="http://www.2000adonline.com/">2000ad</a> since 1977. So great news, a series about zombies in blistering HD quality &#8211; ok audio not that great but still great HD quality. Only six episodes though. What a shame. The series is absolutely fantastic. Its already available in the U.K.via <a href="http://walkingdead.fxuk.com/">U.K.FX.com</a> which is exactly what we were after &#8211; long gone are the days of waiting years for a new series / film in the u.k., now its instant. The main character to boot is &#8220;Egg&#8221; from the old series <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0168596/">&#8220;cold feet&#8221;</a>. He has an affected a transatlantic accent but the end result is still good. Obviously Im going to wax lyrical about a zombie series &#8211; its one of a first, but it really is good. If I could level a criticism at it &#8211; the plot wallowed a touch in episodes 3, but other than that it seems to tick along nicely in as you would expect a classic post apocalyptic scenario. On the zombie film scale of things the gore factor is fairly tame but nicely realistic. A good blend. The shooting is really well done with nice touches of atmosphere and realism &#8211; reminiscent although nowhere near as post nuclear as the Road. Im told by an expert that the comics get very dark indeed featuring very controversial plot lines &#8211; so Im presuming the series wont be going there. So Quality &#8211; check, Actors &#8211; check and plot &#8211; check. Its all good. Well worth seeking out if you a confirmed horror freak like myself.
<br/><br/>]]></content:encoded>
